# Cryosophila warscewiczii

Cryosophila warscewiczii is a species of flowering plant in the family Arecaceae, endemic to Central America. It is a tree with palmate leaves, growing to 10 meters in height with trunk 10â€“15 cm. in diameter above its enlarged base. Much of the trunk bears spines transformed from roots.
Synonyms
* Acanthorrhiza warscewiczii H.Wendl.
* Cryosophila albida
